cz.syntea.xdef

Interface XDDocument

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<XDValue>, XDValue, XDValueID, XXNode

    public interface XDDocument
extends XXNode
    Provides processing of given X-definition. For processing of X-definition you must create and instance of XDDocument created from XDPool with given X-definition in which is defined root (starting point) for next processing. Before starting of process you can set parameters of processing (variables, properties, standard input and output streams, user objects). The document can be used for validation and processing of the input XML data ("xparse" methods) or for construction of a XML object (methods "xcreate"). Note that XDDocument is the root node of processing and it is the extension of the interface XXNode. You can read of or set to variables of a XDPool by methods of XXNode:

    XXNode.getVariable(String), XXNode.setVariable(String, Object), XXNode.setUserObject(Object), XXNode.getUserObject(), XXNode.getUserObject(), XXNode.setXDContext(org.w3c.dom.Node node). XXNode.getXDContext().

    Typical example of validation:

    
 //get instance of XDDocument with X-definition given by name
 XDDocument xDoc = xp.createXDDocument(name);
 ArrayReporter reporter = new ArrayReporter(); // here will be written errors
 ... set variables if necessary - see XXNode
 Element el = xd.xparse(sourceXml, reporter); //validate and process data
 //now we have root element of parsed source data errors in variable el
 //and list of errors in reporter
 //test if an error was reported
 if (reporter.errorWarnings()) {//error or warning reported?
     reporter.getReportReader().printReports(System.err);
 } else {//no errors
     ... get variables if necessary - see XXNode
     ....
 }

    Typical example of construction:

    
 //get instance of XDDocument with X-definition given by name
 XDDocument xDoc = xp.createXDDocument(name);
 ArrayReporter reporter = new ArrayReporter(); // here will be written errors
 ... set data source see XXNode
 //construct required element.
 Element el = xd.xcreate(nsuri, //namespace of required model or null
   name, // name of required model (in given X-definition)
   reporter);
